12508#define WWDG_CFR_W_Msk (0x7FUL << WWDG_CFR_W_Pos)
12509#define WWDG_CFR_W WWDG_CFR_W_Msk
12510#define WWDG_CFR_W_0 (0x01UL << WWDG_CFR_W_Pos)
12511#define WWDG_CFR_W_1 (0x02UL << WWDG_CFR_W_Pos)
12512#define WWDG_CFR_W_2 (0x04UL << WWDG_CFR_W_Pos)
12513#define WWDG_CFR_W_3 (0x08UL << WWDG_CFR_W_Pos)
12514#define WWDG_CFR_W_4 (0x10UL << WWDG_CFR_W_Pos)
12515#define WWDG_CFR_W_5 (0x20UL << WWDG_CFR_W_Pos)
12516#define WWDG_CFR_W_6 (0x40UL << WWDG_CFR_W_Pos)
12518#define WWDG_CFR_WDGTB_Pos (11U)
12519#define WWDG_CFR_WDGTB_Msk (0x7UL << WWDG_CFR_WDGTB_Pos)
12520#define WWDG_CFR_WDGTB WWDG_CFR_WDGTB_Msk
12521#define WWDG_CFR_WDGTB_0 (0x1UL << WWDG_CFR_WDGTB_Pos)
12522#define WWDG_CFR_WDGTB_1 (0x2UL << WWDG_CFR_WDGTB_Pos)
12523#define WWDG_CFR_WDGTB_2 (0x4UL << WWDG_CFR_WDGTB_Pos)
12525#define WWDG_CFR_EWI_Pos (9U)
12526#define WWDG_CFR_EWI_Msk (0x1UL << WWDG_CFR_EWI_Pos)
12527#define WWDG_CFR_EWI WWDG_CFR_EWI_Msk
12529/******************* Bit definition for WWDG_SR register ********************/
12530#define WWDG_SR_EWIF_Pos (0U)
12531#define WWDG_SR_EWIF_Msk (0x1UL << WWDG_SR_EWIF_Pos)
12532#define WWDG_SR_EWIF WWDG_SR_EWIF_Msk

13110/******************************************************************************/
13111/* For a painless codes migration between the STM32G4xx device product */
13112/* lines, the aliases defined below are put in place to overcome the */
13113/* differences in the interrupt handlers and IRQn definitions. */
13114/* No need to update developed interrupt code when moving across */
13115/* product lines within the same STM32G4 Family */
13116/******************************************************************************/
13117
13118/* Aliases for __IRQn */
13119#define TIM7_DAC_IRQn TIM7_IRQn
13120#define COMP4_5_6_IRQn COMP4_IRQn
13121
13122/* Aliases for __IRQHandler */
13123#define TIM7_DAC_IRQHandler TIM7_IRQHandler
13124#define COMP4_5_6_IRQHandler COMP4_IRQHandler
13125

13127}
13128#endif /* __cplusplus */
